  <section>
    <h2>With Wizard Forms</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <p>When used inside (or referenced by) a <code>form[data-wizard]</code>, the <code>wizard.js</code> controller auto-syncs <code>nav.steps</code> state as the user navigates steps. Point the form to the nav using <code>data-wizard-steps="#id"</code>, or place the <code>nav.steps</code> inside the form for auto-discovery.</p>
      <p>The wizard automatically:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Sets <code>data-completed</code> on all steps before the current one</li>
        <li>Sets <code>aria-current="step"</code> on the current step</li>
        <li>Clears attributes from future steps</li>
        <li>Hides conditional steps when they don't apply</li>
      </ul>
    </layout-text>

