  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <ul>
        <li><code>aria-current="step"</code> on the active <code>&lt;li&gt;</code> announces the current step to screen readers</li>
        <li><code>aria-label</code> on the <code>&lt;nav&gt;</code> identifies the navigation purpose</li>
        <li><code>&lt;ol&gt;</code> conveys ordered sequence to assistive technology</li>
        <li>Completed steps with <code>&lt;a&gt;</code> links are keyboard-navigable</li>
        <li>When used with <code>wizard.js</code>, step changes are announced via a live region</li>
        <li>Future steps (no attributes) have muted visual treatment — not interactive, not focusable</li>
      </ul>
    </layout-text>
